  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Safeguarding Disaster Affected Women&apos;s Health and Hygeine in Sri Lanka</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Women affected by natural disasters, such as the flooding in the southern, western and eastern and Sabragamuwa provinces of Sri Lanka in 2018 and 2019, often face difficulties accessing sexual and reproductive health commodities such as sanitary items. This project seeks to preposition the stock of such commodities to ensure they are available for distribution during disasters, thus safeguarding the health and hygiene of vulnerable women and pregnant mothers.</narrative>
  </description>
